Zilliz Cloud's metric charts provide performance data on resource usage, queries per second (
), request results, and data operations, offering granular analysis within a specific time range.
For details on each metric chart, refer to
tab allows for two types of window sizes.

: Choose from a set of pre-defined time periods relative to your current time. Using relative time ranges allows you to check metrics in a periodical and convenient way, without needing to enter the specific start and end time. Your choices include:
: Enter the exact start time and end time. Using absolute range allows you to control the metrics you see in a more fine-tuned way.
The time difference between the start and the end time should be greater than 10 minutes.
Zilliz Cloud offers metric charts for monitoring cluster performance from various aspects. For a quick overview of available metrics, refer to
To view metric charts for resource usage, locate the
tab. These charts provide a snapshot of the cluster's resource usage, including computation, capacity, and storage.
: Measures computational power usage relative to the total.
: Indicates used capacity as a percentage of total, measured per second over time.
100%: When the used CU capacity hits 100%, Zilliz Cloud disables data writing and triggers SDK errors. To restore normal functionality,

To view metric charts for requests, locate the
tab. These charts provide a snapshot of the cluster's request performance by showing the proportion of successful and failed requests.
: The percentage of successful requests in all requests per second.
: The percentage of timeout requests in all requests per second.
To view metric charts for entities, locate the
tab. These charts provide a snapshot of the cluster's entity data by indicating the current entity count and the rate at which new entity data is being inserted.
: The count of entities loaded in the cluster.
: The count of entities inserted per second.
